Agent capabilities can be specified via the bamboo-capabilties.properties file as specified in https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO033/Configuring+Remote+Agent+Capabilities+via+bamboo-capabilities.properties Now if the location of the capabiltiy is a symlink, then it is registered as a multiple depending on the number of symlinks. 

*Steps to replicate*
# Create a symlink to a JDK installation
{code}
ln -s /usr/local/java/jdk1.7.0_17 sultanjdk
{code}
# This has created a symlink sultanjdk. Add a capability:
{code}
system.jdk.sultanjdk=/home/sultan/sultanjdk
{code}
OR
{code}
system.jdk.sultan+jdk=/usr/local/java/jdk1.7.0_17
{code}
# upon restart of the agent, two capabilities are registered as per the screenshot

We have to delete one of them and then subsequent restarts will only register one. It will be great if bamboo can just scan for one of the two.

